\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Type-I seesaw $(y, M_R)$-plane against NuFit-6.0 oscillation anchors. The shaded band marks the natural-seesaw region between the $m_3 \approx 0.05$~eV atmospheric contour and the $m_\nu \lesssim 0.1$~eV cosmology cap. The star marks the canonical Type-I anchor $(y_{\rm  top}, \Lambda _{\rm  ADW}\!\sim \! 10^{16}~{\rm  GeV})$; the diamond marks the Wave-2 lower-scan anchor. Lean reference: \texttt  {MajoranaRung.seesawNeutrinoMass\_strictMono\_inv\_M\_R}.}}{2}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
