\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Effective Majorana mass $m_{\beta \beta }$ against the lightest neutrino mass $m_{\rm  lightest}$. Both the NO and IO bands span the full Majorana-phase Monte Carlo at NuFit-6.0~\cite  {NuFit60} best-fit angles. Horizontal bands: KamLAND-Zen 800~\cite  {KamLANDZen800} current 90\% CL bound (28-122~meV; NME spread) and LEGEND-1000 99.7\% CL projected discovery reach (9-21~meV)~\cite  {LEGEND1000}. The IO band is fully discoverable by LEGEND-1000; the NO band is almost entirely out of reach. The result is embedding-agnostic across I/II/III. Lean reference: \texttt  {NeutrinoMixing.PMNSMatrix}.}}{4}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:m-bb-vs-m-lightest}{{2}{4}{Effective Majorana mass $\mbb $ against the lightest neutrino mass $m_{\rm lightest}$. Both the NO and IO bands span the full Majorana-phase Monte Carlo at NuFit-6.0~\cite {NuFit60} best-fit angles. Horizontal bands: KamLAND-Zen 800~\cite {KamLANDZen800} current 90\% CL bound (28-122~meV; NME spread) and LEGEND-1000 99.7\% CL projected discovery reach (9-21~meV)~\cite {LEGEND1000}. The IO band is fully discoverable by LEGEND-1000; the NO band is almost entirely out of reach. The result is embedding-agnostic across I/II/III. Lean reference: \texttt {NeutrinoMixing.PMNSMatrix}}{figure.2}{}}
